This paper proposes a meta-learning method for multi-label classification tasks in natural language processing. The paper discusses the use of a meta-learner to jointly learn training policies and prediction policies for different labels, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve fine-grained entity typing and text classification, which are both subfields of natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE) in the experiments. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.NE, in that order.
